                " \n \nASSETS CONTROLLER\nListing reference: spar_000452\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 6 December 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Wholesale & Retail Trade\nJob category: Others: Transport and Logistics\nLocation: Durban\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: Yes\nIntroduction\nA position has become available for an Assets Controller to join our dynamic team.\n \nJob description\nTo control, collate and maintain assets and statistical procedures in the warehouse so as to provide exceptional service to both internal and external customers.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nCompile asset statistics and reports on asset movement.\nComplete audit of assets.\nConduct asset counts (stock take of assets).\nControl the LUG and pallet holding period and documentation.\nControl the repair and/or purchasing of assets.\nFile asset records and documentation received from retailers.\nMaintain supplier service level agreements.\nProcess Transfer hire agreements.\nUpdate all asset transactions on Portfolio Systems.\nManage expenses and recoveries in line with budget.\nMonitor daily Asset Management reports.\nBuild and maintain effective customer relationships.\nEffective communication with customers (internal and/or external).\nMonitor professional service to customers (internal or external).\nConduct store visits.\nInvestigate SHEQX incidents in department.\nMaintain housekeeping of department.\nMaintain Food Safety Standards with regards to cold-boxes and crates.\nCreate and manage SAP expense purchase orders for Inbound.\nManage the recycling initiatives i.e., cardboard, plastic, used oil and any other recycling drives.\nA working knowledge of SAP will be advantageous.\nAny other reasonable tasks.\n \nMinimum requirements\nMatric.\nA National Diploma in Transport Management will be an added advantage.\n2 years\u2019 experience in a warehouse environment.\nExperience leading a team.\nSAP knowledge advantageous.\nComputer literacy essential (MS Excel is essential).\nAttention to details and accuracy.\nGood communication skills.\nAbility to communicate with internal and external customers department, management, and service providers.\nAttention to Detail (Work Standards).\nContinuous Improvement Orientated.\nEffective Decision-Making Skills.\nPlanning and Organizing Skills.\nFlexible to work overtime including weekends when required. \n \nKindly note: All applications are to be submitted through the Careers Site and Pnet. Please refrain from calling the Distribution Centre (DC) or emailing applications directly.\n \n\u201cYour application and all personal information provided herein is protected under the Protection of Personal Information Act (4 of 2013), hereinafter referred to as the \u201cAct\u201d.\n  The SPAR Group LTD, with its head offices at 22 Chancery Lane in Pinetown, is collecting this information to enable us to facilitate your application and /or assess your suitability for the advertised position. This information will be used for this purpose only and disposed of thereafter, unless you consent to the information being retained for marketing purposes.\nWhere shortlisted, your information will be retained for a period of 3 months and disposed of immediately thereafter if you are unsuccessful in your application. Where employment is offered, it will be retained as part of your employee portfolio and secured accordingly.\nThis information is given to us, by you, voluntarily and of your own free will.\nIf you do not wish to provide us with this information, are unable to do so, or object to it being used, it will result in the disqualification of your application.\nIn the course of the recruitment process, and for matters related to your application only, we may share your information with third parties.\nYou have the right to access this information while in our possession and make corrections if necessary.\nYou have the right to lodge a complaint via email with the office of the Information Regulator, at complaints.IR@justice.gov.za, if you are unhappy with the manner in which we deal with your information.\n \nBy submitting your application, you hereby declare your understanding of the aforementioned information and consent to the processing of your information in accordance with the Act, as well as the processing of any further personal information requested by us in the future including but not limited to, banking details, criminal history and credit reports /financial history information.\u201d\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nREGIONAL RETAIL OPERATIONS MANAGER (D) \u2013 BUILD IT\nListing reference: spar_000453\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 17 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: FMCG & Supply Management\nJob category: Other: FMCG, Retail, Wholesale and Supply Chain\nLocation: Boksburg\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: Yes\nIntroduction\nSPAR North Rand is looking for a suitably qualified and experienced Regional Retail Operations Manager (D) \u2013 Build it to join our dynamic team.\n \nJob description\nPURPOSE:\nThe Retail Operations Manager is responsible for growing DC and Retail Sales through providing a comprehensive business consulting service to our Build It Stores\n \nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS:\nEnsuring that all Build It stores are maintained at a level of excellence\nAssisting Build It stores to be profitable\nMeasuring business performance through the use of information technology\nAnalysis of financial results.\nAdvising on modern retail trends in hardware utilizing category management\nPerforming store audits through structured store visits and the circulation of written reports to regional and national office where appropriate\nPreparing business plans for stores.\nImproving image and standards of all stores.\n \nMinimum requirements\nMatric Certificate\nBusiness/Financial Management Diploma\nMCSE or similar tertiary IT qualification \u2013 mandatory\nRetail systems qualification (IQ Enterprise)\nCustomer focused\nNegotiation skills\nInterpersonal skills\nProject management skills\nInnovative\nStress tolerance and integrity\nRetail Management experience preferably at senior management level would be an advantage\nNew store development skills\nThe ability to develop an open, sincere and trusting relationship with our retailers\nUnderstanding of tax laws\nHigh energy level and the ability to operate under pressure\nAbility to work within a team whilst able to work independently\nComputer literate\nDriver\u2019s license a necessity\nMust be willing to travel extensively\n \nSPAR North Rand is an equal opportunity employer. All positions are advertised in accordance with the company\u2019s Employment Equity Policy.\n \nCLOSING DATE: 17 November 2023\n \nKindly note: All applications are to be submitted through the Careers Site and Pnet. Please refrain from calling the Distribution Centre (DC) or emailing applications directly.\n\n \n\u201cYour application and all personal information provided herein is protected under the Protection of Personal Information Act (4 of 2013), hereinafter referred to as the \u201cAct\u201d.\n \nThe SPAR Group LTD, with its head offices at 22 Chancery Lane in Pinetown, is collecting this information to enable us to facilitate your application and /or assess your suitability for the advertised position. This information will be used for this purpose only and disposed of thereafter, unless you consent to the information being retained for marketing purposes.\nWhere shortlisted, your information will be retained for a period of 3 months and disposed of immediately thereafter if you are unsuccessful in your application. Where employment is offered, it will be retained as part of your employee portfolio and secured accordingly.\nThis information is given to us, by you, voluntarily and of your own free will.\nIf you do not wish to provide us with this information, are unable to do so, or object to it being used, it will result in the disqualification of your application.\nIn the course of the recruitment process, and for matters related to your application only, we may share your information with third parties.\nYou have the right to access this information while in our possession and make corrections if necessary.\nYou have the right to lodge a complaint via email with the office of the Information Regulator, at complaints.IR@justice.gov.za, if you are unhappy with the manner in which we deal with your information.\n \nBy submitting your application, you hereby declare your understanding of the aforementioned information and consent to the processing of your information in accordance with the Act, as well as the processing of any further personal information requested by us in the future including but not limited to, banking details, criminal history and credit reports /financial history information.\u201d\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "NEW BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT MANAGER\nListing reference: spar_000450\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 10 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Wholesale & Retail Trade\nJob category: Business Development\nLocation: Durban\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: Yes\nIntroduction\nA position has become available for a New Business Development Manager to join our dynamic team.\n \nJob description\nBased at the SPAR KZN DC, the successful incumbent will secure new business opportunities for the Build it division through the identification of strategically placed sites or conversions, and selection of suitable retailers.\n \nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS:\nEnsuring that Build it has a strong presence in the retail property development industry.\nEnsuring Build it is a preferred choice with landlords and developers for new developments.\nPursuing conversion opportunities to grow the retail footprint for the region.\nEvaluation of prospective sites for new Build it stores.\nIdentify funding opportunities for new and existing Retailers and sites.\nConduct feasibility studies for new developments, store sales, leases, etc. as the need arises/requested by management.\nPresentation of selected sites to Property Committee and Regional Committee for membership approval.\nAll matters relating to leases within the region over which the incumbent will have domain including queries, renewals, new leases, etc.\nInterview and evaluation of prospective Retailers.\nInitiation and management of the change of ownership within the region of the incumbent.\nConduct regional benchmarking exercises.\n \nMinimum requirements\nRETAIL PROPERTY EXPERTISE:\n\nProperty related tertiary qualification relevant to the role.\nFirm understanding of retail property best practices and fundamentals.\nFirm understanding of commercial terms and current trends in the retail property market.\n \nFINANCIAL EXPERTISE:\nVersed in analysis of financial statements particularly cashflow statement.\nFirm understanding of financing options.\nAbility to undertake and interpret financial feasibility studies.\n \nMARKET KNOWLEDGE:\nFirm understanding of macro-economic drivers of retail.\nGrasp of retail benchmarks and key drivers.\nAbility to interpret demographic data and conduct market studies.\n3-5 years relevant experience.\nCommand of MS Office bouquet to an intermediate level.\nKnowledge and understanding of property law.\nHigh level of numeracy skills.\nBuilding strategic working relationships.\nExcellent communication skills.\nDeadline orientated.\nInfluencing skills.\nInformation monitoring.\nQuality orientated.\nAccuracy and attention to detail.\nValid driver\u2019s license and own vehicle.\n \nKindly note: All applications are to be submitted through the Careers Site and Pnet. Please refrain from calling the Distribution Centre (DC) or emailing applications directly.\n \nClosing Date: 10 November 2023\n \n\u201cYour application and all personal information provided herein is protected under the Protection of Personal Information Act (4 of 2013), hereinafter referred to as the \u201cAct\u201d.\n\nThe SPAR Group LTD, with its head offices at 22 Chancery Lane in Pinetown, is collecting this information to enable us to facilitate your application and /or assess your suitability for the advertised position. This information will be used for this purpose only and disposed of thereafter, unless you consent to the information being retained for marketing purposes.\nWhere shortlisted, your information will be retained for a period of 3 months and disposed of immediately thereafter if you are unsuccessful in your application. Where employment is offered, it will be retained as part of your employee portfolio and secured accordingly.\nThis information is given to us, by you, voluntarily and of your own free will.\nIf you do not wish to provide us with this information, are unable to do so, or object to it being used, it will result in the disqualification of your application.\nIn the course of the recruitment process, and for matters related to your application only, we may share your information with third parties.\nYou have the right to access this information while in our possession and make corrections if necessary.\nYou have the right to lodge a complaint via email with the office of the Information Regulator, at complaints.IR@justice.gov.za, if you are unhappy with the manner in which we deal with your information.\nBy submitting your application, you hereby declare your understanding of the aforementioned information and consent to the processing of your information in accordance with the Act, as well as the processing of any further personal information requested by us in the future including but not limited to, banking details, criminal history and credit reports /financial history information.\u201d\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "2023/24 GRADUATE PLACEMENT PROGRAMME\nListing reference: spar_000451\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 10 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: FMCG & Supply Management\nJob category: Graduate\nLocation: Boksburg\nContract: Fixed Term Contract\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: Yes\n \nIntroduction\nThe 2023 Graduate Placement Programme (Internship) has opened, SPAR North Rand will be sourcing 10 Graduates that have completed relevant qualifications from Higher Education and Training Institutions (HETI).\n \nJob description\nSKILLS/KNOWLEDGE/EXPERIENCE\nMatric plus a relevant Diploma/Degree\nGood communication skills\nAccurate and dependable\nWillingness to learn.\nAttention to detail.\nAdministrative skills\nWillingness to embrace SPAR values: Passion, Family, and Entrepreneurship\n \nMinimum requirements\nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS\nSupply Chain/Logistics Management\nReal Estate Management/Property Management\nFinancial Accounting/Management\nInformation Technology\nHuman Resources Management Marketing\nProject Management\n \n \nSPAR North Rand is an equal opportunity employer. All positions are placed in accordance with the company\u2019s Employment Equity Plan.\n \nKindly note: All applications are to be submitted through the Careers Site and Pnet. Please refrain from calling the Distribution Centre (DC) or emailing applications directly.\n \nClosing Date: 10 November 2023\n \n\u201cYour application and all personal information provided herein is protected under the Protection of Personal Information Act (4 of 2013), hereinafter referred to as the \u201cAct\u201d.\n  The SPAR Group LTD, with its head offices at 22 Chancery Lane in Pinetown, is collecting this information to enable us to facilitate your application and /or assess your suitability for the advertised position. This information will be used for this purpose only and disposed of thereafter, unless you consent to the information being retained for marketing purposes.\nWhere shortlisted, your information will be retained for a period of 3 months and disposed of immediately thereafter if you are unsuccessful in your application. Where employment is offered, it will be retained as part of your employee portfolio and secured accordingly.\nThis information is given to us, by you, voluntarily and of your own free will.\nIf you do not wish to provide us with this information, are unable to do so, or object to it being used, it will result in the disqualification of your application.\nIn the course of the recruitment process, and for matters related to your application only, we may share your information with third parties.\nYou have the right to access this information while in our possession and make corrections if necessary.\nYou have the right to lodge a complaint via email with the office of the Information Regulator, at complaints.IR@justice.gov.za, if you are unhappy with the manner in which we deal with your information.\n \nBy submitting your application, you hereby declare your understanding of the aforementioned information and consent to the processing of your information in accordance with the Act, as well as the processing of any further personal information requested by us in the future including but not limited to, banking details, criminal history and credit reports /financial history information.\u201d\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
