                " \n \n \n \n \nFINANCE MANAGER- COMMERCIAL FCM1013\nLocation: Paarl\n \nPurpose: The successful candidate will be responsible for all aspects of financial/commercial management of the SA Sales Division.  Manage, coordinate and analyse all financial related matters, ensure that reporting is done accurately and internal control systems are exercised in order to mitigate the associated risk. The incumbent will also manage a team who provide finance and commercial related support to the SA sales team.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nBCom or BAcc (Hons) and completed articles\nCA(SA) will be advantageous\nAt least 5 year\u2019s financial management experience (preferably in an FMCG environment)\nExtensive knowledge of financial management concepts, principles and procedures\nExperience in the Wine/Liquor industry will be advantageous\n2 to 3 years People Management experience\n \nSkills Required:\nAbility to communicate in English on an advanced level\nMS Office proficiency on an advance level (Excel, Word and Powerpoint)\nSAP and Qlikview experience will be advantageous\nRelationship management\nAbility to network and form new networks\nCommercial business acumen\nConfident and accomplished presentation skills\nSound interpersonal skills and the ability to work in a team and also cross functional\nStrong analytical skills and a sound grasp of systems\nSelf-starter and ability to take initiative and work independently\n \nJob Summary:\nFinancial management\nDelivery of RSA Commercial P&L\nLead the annual financial budgeting process for the division\nManage, coordinate and control the budget\nCompile monthly financial reports\nManage OPEX, A&P, Discounts and P&L associated costs and relevant variances\nBusiness analysis & reporting\nBusiness improvement projects\nGeneral financial administration\nCost management\nStatutory compliance and risk management\nManage and Lead the SA Finance Support Team\n \n \nPreference will be given to EE candidates\n \n Closing date for applications:  27 October 2023\n \nPlease note that any personal information that you shared will be used for the purposes of applying for a role with KWV as advertised above. This information may be shared with authorised Warshay Investments (Pty) Ltd (\u201cKWV\u201d) representatives (internal and contracted external parties) as required. Should you have any questions related to how we process your personal information, please refer to the privacy policy.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "PROCESS ARTISAN PA1110\nLocation: Paarl\nPurpose: To maintain and improve manufacturing process equipment and ensure that such machinery operates optimally in a clean and organized environment.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nQualified artisan with N3, Millwright with good electronic skills\n5 years\u2019 experience in maintenance of equipment in FMCG/Beverage industry\nExperience in maintenance and operation of electronic packaging equipment\nExperience in working on filling machines, labelling machines, conveyors, printers and glue units\nKnowledge and understanding of relevant statutory regulations (OHS Act, HACCP)\nMust be willing to work overtime and shift work when operationally required\n \nKnowledge required:\nWorld class manufacturing principles with a specific understanding of lean manufacturing\nIdentify and analyze process challenges/shortcomings\nRoot cause analysis tools and implementation of solutions\nClear understanding of the role of a technician within a FMCG production environment\nStrong technical aptitude fault finding.\nMachine specialist in bottling environment would be advantageous\nKnowledge of preventative maintenance system\nBasic PLC programming would be advantageous\nGood problem solving skills, electrical wiring, and problem solving.\nBasic computer skills and good written and verbal communication skills (English & Afrikaans)\n \nJob Summary:\nPerform daily scheduled maintenance activities in accordance with safety procedures and department working standard\nAnalyse technical problems immediately as and when they arise on the packaging lines & process areas and make the necessary repairs and/or corrective measures\nOptimize available resources, contain cost, improve machine productivity\nProject planning and execution of technical improvements.\n \nPreference will be given to EE candidates\n \nTo apply, please email your CV to: recruitment@kwv.co.za\n \nClosing date:  25 October 2023\n \nPlease note that any personal information that you share will be used for the purposes of applying for a role with KWV as advertised above. This information may be shared with authorised Warshay Investments (Pty) Ltd (\u201cKWV\u201d) representatives (internal and contracted external parties) as required. Should you have any questions related to how we process your personal information, please refer to the privacy policy.",
                "CREDITORS CLERK CC1110\nLocation: Paarl\n \nPurpose: Timeous and accurate processing of creditor invoices and credit notes to ensure accurate payments of all creditors according to company policy and procedures.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS:\nGrade 12 with accounting as a subject\nA relevant tertiary qualification will be advantageous\n3-5 years relevant experience in a financial environment preferable Creditors\nExperience in SAP will be advantageous\n \nSKILLS REQUIRED:\nSound numerical skills\nSelf-starter with ability to work in a team as well as independently\nComputer literate on an advanced level (Word, Excel, etc)\nProblem solving skills and handle pressure well\nOrganised and deadline driven\nCustomer service orientation\nAbility to communicate in English (verbal and written)\n \nJOB SUMMARY:\nVerification of Invoices for correctness\nProcessing of invoices timeously for payment\nHandling telephone enquiries regarding creditors\nFiling of documents\nReconciliation of monthly statements\n \nPreference will be given to EE candidates\n \nFor Internal applications, please email your CV to: recruitment@kwv.co.za\n \nClosing date:  25 October 2023\n \nPlease note that any personal information that you shared will be used for the purposes of applying for a role with KWV as advertised above. This information may be shared with authorised Warshay Investments (Pty) Ltd (\u201cKWV\u201d) representatives (internal and contracted external parties) as required. Should you have any questions related to how we process your personal information, please refer to the privacy policy."
