                " \n \n \nFOOD TECHNOLOGY INTERN\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/23\nReference Number: PRE231016-1\nJob Title: Food Technology Intern\nDepartment: Production\nSite: 655 - Outeniqua\nJob Type Classification: Internship\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: George\nLocation \u2013 Province: Western Cape\n \nJob Description\nTo ensure that a quality product is produced in accordance with company specifications.\n \nResponsibilities:\nQuality management\nAudits\nTechnical support / Troubleshooting\nOn the job training\nFood safety\n \nQualification Requirements\nMatric\n \nExperience Requirements\nIn progress: National Diploma: Food Technology\n \nOther Requirements:\nPressurised environment\n6-day position\nFactory environment (hot and noisy)\nRequired to work Saturdays, Sundays and Public Holidays as per shift roster\n \nKey Outputs\nLegislation\nQuality management principles\nProduct / Portfolio\nAnalytical thinking\nCommunication\nDecision making ability\nNumerical ability\nProactivity\nSupportiveness\nInnovation/Continuous Improvements\nTeamwork\nAccountability\nSense of urgency/results orientation\nRespect\n \n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.",
                "ARTISAN ASSISTANT: MAINTENANCE\n \nDetails\nClosing Date: 2023/10/18\nReference Number: PRE231013-2\nJob Title: Artisan Assistant: Maintenance\nDepartment: Maintenance\nSite: 670 - BRB East London\nJob Type Classification: Fixed Term Contract\nLocation \u2013 Country: South Africa\nLocation - Town / City: East London\nLocation \u2013 Province: Eastern Cape\n \nJob Description\n \nPurpose of the job:\nTo maintain the overall effectiveness of equipment and plant on site.\nAre you a target driven individual with high attention to detail and accuracy?\nDo you enjoy working in a highly pressurised environment which operates 24/7/365 days a year?\nDo you have 1-2 years\u2019 experience as an artisan assistant?\n \nQualification Requirements   \nQualifications: \nA matric certificate and the willingness to further your studies to ultimately meet the requirements of the position is essential.\n \nExperience Requirements    \nDo you possess the following essential competencies?\nIndustry knowledge\nLegislation (OHS Act)\nWorking with people\nPlanning and organising\n \nKey Outputs   \nOther Requirements:\nRequired to work rotational shifts\nRequired to work outside of normal working hours (after hours and over time)\nWorking with and on heavy equipment and plant (mechanical and electrical)\n \n \nPolicy\nPlease note that it is company policy to promote from within wherever possible, hence internal applicants will be given priority. We recruit and appoint in line with our Employment Equity Goals and objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
